        "summary":  "Google introduced DiffusionGemma, an open-source 26B Mixture of Experts model using text diffusion technology that generates entire blocks of 256 tokens in parallel rather than sequentially, achieving up to 4x faster text generation on GPUs and over 1,000 tokens per second on NVIDIA H100 hardware. The model requires only 3.8B active parameters during inference and fits within 18GB VRAM when quantized, making it viable on consumer GPUs. The researchers note a quality trade-off ΓÇö output quality is lower than standard Gemma 4 ΓÇö making the model best suited for speed-optimized, local, low-concurrency inference tasks like code infilling and inline editing.",
