        "source":  "MIT Technology Review",
        "url":  "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/06/30/1139987/claude-science-is-anthropics-newest-flagship-product/",
        "date":  "2026-06-30",
        "theme":  "Models",
        "summary":  "Anthropic launched Claude Science, a specialized AI product for scientific research that runs autonomously on high-level instructions and includes tools for computational biology and drug development. The system writes and executes code on computing clusters with an emphasis on reproducibility. Anthropic plans to use Claude Science for its own drug research while seeking pharmaceutical partnerships ahead of an anticipated IPO.",
        "execSummary":  "Anthropic\u0027s Claude Science marks a strategic move to dominate AI-driven research automation, directly challenging Google DeepMind\u0027s historical leadership in science AI ΓÇö signaled by Anthropic\u0027s hire of Nobel-linked researcher John Jumper. For enterprise leaders in pharma, biotech, or any R\u0026D-intensive sector, this signals that autonomous AI scientific agents are moving from prototype to product. The key caveat: Anthropic\u0027s own benchmark places the model at \u0027second-year graduate student\u0027 capability level, meaning expert human oversight remains essential for high-stakes research decisions.",
